Job_Description: Responsible for designing  building and overseeing the deployment and operation of technology architecture  solutions and software to capture  manage  store and utilize structured and unstructured data from internal and external sources. Establishes and builds processes and structures based on business and technical requirements to channel data from multiple inputs  route appropriately and store using any combination of distributed (cloud) structures  local databases  and other applicable storage forms as required. Develops technical tools and programming that leverage artificial intelligence  machine learning and big-data techniques to cleanse  organize and transform data and to maintain  defend and update data structures and integrity on an automated basis. Creates and establishes design standards and assurance processes for software  systems and applications development to ensure compatibility and operability of data connections  flows and storage requirements. Reviews internal and external business and product requirements for data operations and activity and suggests changes and upgrades to systems and storage to accommodate ongoing needs. Work with data modelers/analysts to understand the business problems they are trying to solve then create or augment data assets to feed their analysis. Has in-depth experience  knowledge and skills in own discipline. Usually determines own work priorities. Acts as resource for colleagues with less experience. Develops data structures and pipelines aligned to established standards and guidelines to organize  collect  standardize and transform data that helps generate insights and address reporting needs. Focuses on ensuring data quality during ingest  processing as well as final load to the target tables. Creates standard ingestion frameworks for structured and unstructured data as well as checking and reporting on the quality of the data being processed. Creates standard methods for end users / downstream applications to consume data including but not limited to database views  extracts and Application Programming Interfaces. Develops and maintains information systems (e.g.  data warehouses  data lakes) including data access Application Programming Interfaces. Participates in the implementation of solutions via data architecture  data engineering  or data manipulation on both on-prem platforms like Kubernetes and Teradata as well as Cloud platforms like Databricks.  Determines the appropriate storage platform across different on-prem (minIO and Teradata) and Cloud (AWS S3  Redshift) depending on the privacy  access and sensitivity requirements. Understands the data lineage from source to the final semantic layer along with the transformation rules applied to enable faster troubleshooting and impact analysis during changes.  Collaborates with technology and platform management partners to optimize data sourcing and processing rules to ensure appropriate data quality as well as process optimization. Creates and establishes design standards and assurance processes for software  systems and applications development to ensure compatibility and operability of data connections  flows and storage requirements. Reviews internal and external business and product requirements for data operations and activity and suggests changes and upgrades to systems and storage to accommodate ongoing needs. Develops strategies for data acquisition  archive recovery  and database implementation. Manages data migrations/conversions and troubleshooting data processing issues. Understands the data sensitivity  customer data privacy rules and regulations and applies them consistently in all Information Lifecycle Management activities. Identifies and reacts to system notification and log to ensure quality standards for databases and applications. Solves abstract problems beyond single development language or situation by reusing data file and flags already set.  Solves critical issues and shares knowledge such as trends  aggregate  quantity volume regarding specific data sources. Company Description  At AECOM  we’re delivering a better world.  We believe infrastructure creates opportunity for everyone. Whether it’s improving your commute  keeping the lights on  providing access to clean water or transforming skylines  our work helps people and communities thrive.  Our clients trust us to bring together the best people  ideas  technical expertise and digital solutions to our work in transportation  buildings  water  the environment and new energy. We’re one global team – 47 000 strong – driven by a common purpose to deliver a better world.  Here  you will have freedom to grow in a world of opportunity.  We will give you the flexibility you need to do your best work with hybrid work options. Whether you’re working from an AECOM office  remote location or at a client site  you will be working in a dynamic environment where your integrity  entrepreneurial spirit and pioneering mindset are championed.  You will help us foster a culture of equity  diversity and inclusion – a safe and respectful workplace  where we invite everyone to bring their whole selves to work using their unique talents  backgrounds and expertise to create transformational outcomes for our clients.  We will encourage you to grow and develop your career with us through our technical and professional development programs and diverse career opportunities. We believe in leadership at all levels. No matter where you sit in the organization you can make a lasting impact on the projects you work on  the teams and committees you join and our business.  We offer competitive pay and benefits  well-being programs to support you and your family  and the development resources you need to advance your career.  When you join us  you will connect and collaborate with a global network of experts – planners  designers  engineers  scientists  consultants  program and construction managers – leading the change toward a more sustainable and equitable future. Join us and let’s get started.  Job Description  The Solutions Consultant will support AECOM’s Technology Solutions Group Networks team. Candidate will be responsible for sales engineering  installing  configuring and supporting a range of network and wireless equipment with a focus on Passive Optical LAN and WiFi. Solutions Consultant will be client-facing  demonstrating capabilities to clients. Candidate will be expected to independently configure network equipment under the general direction of senior staff members. Candidate will be familiar with various copper and fiber cabling types. Candidate is not required to have deep knowledge or experience with passive optical networking but must have a strong networking background to build upon. The ideal candidate will demonstrate a willingness to learn a variety of local area networking (LAN) technologies  network cabling practices  and communicate in a courteous and professional manner to our clients. The candidate must be highly detail-oriented  organized  and possess analytic and problem-solving abilities. Excellent interpersonal skills as well as verbal and written communication skills are a must. This is a hand-on position which will involve all aspects of network installation to include sales engineering  physical installation  equipment configuration  troubleshooting  and support.  Candidate will be expect to travel (typically no more than once or twice per month) to client sites  primarily within the United States.  Qualifications  The Solutions Consultant must demonstrate experience in implementing and configuring switched network solutions with optional experience with routing and WAN technologies. Network Consultant should be comfortable configuring network equipment from scratch based on requirements for VLANs  QoS  PoE  and STP. Candidate must be proficient with current network technologies and related communications standards. Must be able to review requirements and specifications developed by others and make product and design recommendations. Candidate must be able to provide technical support on network installation projects. Must be able to lift equipment and install in rack as well as climb a ladder.  Responsibilities  + Work with senior team members to develop solutions for clients.  + Present ideas and work directly with clients.  + Physical installation of network components.  + Configure and test network equipment.  + Provide in-person and remote support.  Qualifications   + BA/BS Degree + 8 years of relevant experience or demonstrated equivalency of experience and/or education  + Candidate must be a U.S. citizen.   + Technical network certification such as POL  CCNA  JNCIA  or similar is a plus.  + Experience with WiFi wireless access points and controllers  firewalls  WAN routing  Active Directory  Linux  or VMWare are a plus.  + Experience configuring distributed antenna systems is a plus.  + Located within the Southwestern United States is ideal but not necessary  Additional Information  Ability to lift equipment and install in rack as well as climb a ladder required.  With infrastructure investment accelerating worldwide  our services are in great demand  and there’s never been a better time to be at AECOM! Join us  and you’ll get all the benefits of being a part of a global  publicly traded firm – access to industry-leading technology and thinking and transformational work with big impact and work flexibility.  AECOM provides a wide array of compensation and benefits programs to meet the diverse needs of our employees and their families. We also provide a robust global well-being program. We’re the world’s trusted global infrastructure firm  and we’re in this together – your growth and success are ours too.  As an Equal Opportunity Employer  we believe in each person’s potential  and we’ll help you reach yours.  Join us and let’s get started. Leidos is looking for aerospace hypersonic senior design engineers to support the development and use of numerical analysis tools to design hypersonic weapon concepts in our Eglin AFB  FL location. Candidates will specialize in developing engineering software for hypersonic concept generation and analysis. This includes fast-running aerothermal modeling  computational geometry and meshing  high-speed aerodynamic shape optimization  and system-level multi-objective optimization. Research new design methodologies for hypersonic and high performance weapons systems. Develop novel analysis techniques in computational fluid dynamics  structural dynamics  heat transfer  and shape optimization  as well as coupled multiphysics analysis tools. Develop software tools that push the envelope of today’s modeling and simulation capabilities. Exercise the developed tools on offensive and defensive platforms. Perform trade space analysis  evaluating system and mission performance  and use the knowledge gained to guide the design cycle of new weapons systems to maturity. Conduct wind tunnel and flight tests to validate tools and analysis. This well-supported research environment provides the unique and fulfilling experience of developing innovative ideas from concept  through digital engineering  and onto physical test and evaluation. Work Environment: Be part of a close-knit team of world class experts. The Aerophysics group operates in a small team environment where individual creativity is rewarded  and continuous learning is the norm. Have direct access to DOD personnel and work directly with the organizations developing the most advanced weapons systems in the world. The Destin-Fort Walton Beach and surrounding area is home to world-famous beaches and the ‘salt life’ Emerald Cost lifestyle. May have remote work location opportunities but must be able to work onsite in FL at least approximately 25% of the time. Experience Level: Candidates should have Bachelors of Engineering in Aerospace  Mechanical  or similar and a minimum of 8 years experience in industry  or an MS and 6 years experience. Candidates should be able to make programmatic decisions and perform technical tasks with minimal supervision. Communication Skills: Successful candidates should be able to effectively communicate with Leidos aerodynamics and structural engineers  and interact daily with customers  team members and end users. Must develop a clear understanding of customer goals and objectives and shape work activities to satisfy them. Must present both verbal and written status on a regular basis  and prepare manuscripts for publication at technical conferences and professional journals. Clearance: Must be a U.S. Citizen with active Secret clearance. Desired Knowledge: Computer Languages: Python or MATLAB/SIMULINK  C++ or FORTRAN CFD Software: Cart3D  Kestrel  US3D  FUN3D  OpenFOAM FEA Software: Sierra Tool Suite  LS-DYNA  Nastran  Abaqus  Ansys  etc. Numerical Meshing: Pointwise  TrueGrid  CREATE Capstone  CUBIT  etc. ML: TensorFlow  PyTorch  ScikitLearn  MATLAB AI toolbox  etc. Wind tunnel  flight  or other experimental test planning and safety review experience LInC Electronic Warfare The Leidos pay range for this job level is a general guideline only and not a guarantee of compensation or salary. Frontier Aerospace Corporation conceptualizes  designs  proves and additively manufactures in-space and launch system rocket propulsion thrusters. From concept ideation to product development to qualification testing to customer delivery  we have a proven philosophy and the in-house resources necessary to design  build  test  and deliver reliable  high-performance liquid propellant thrusters for our nation's critical in-space  commercial  civilian  and defense applications. Whether they are used for attitude control  orbit transfer  lunar and exo-moon landing  deep-space missions  or high-thrust divert systems  Frontier's thrusters meet the most demanding requirements. Our customers are hungry for a propulsion supplier who can reliably meet their requirements and who is responsive to their needs. Frontier's mission is to do just that  by advancing breakthrough propulsion technologies and providing industry-leading customer responsiveness. Ultimately  it's our fantastic team of dedicated professionals and hard-working tradespeople who make this a reality. As a small  but rapidly growing company  there are many opportunities for our team members to grow and take on new and exciting responsibilities - to be more than just another worker. Come make a difference and share in our success! Come join our growing team where you will get to make a difference daily by continuing to help build our reputation for quality  responsiveness  and the ability to handle complex products. The successful candidate will be responsible for engineering assignments requiring a wide application of advanced principles  theories and concepts in rocket engine design and development  while working collaboratively with the rest of the team across multiple projects to produce quality thrusters. COMPANY DESCRIPTION AirLife is a respected North American manufacturer and distributor of one of the most comprehensive portfolios of consumable medical devices for anesthesia and respiratory care. The AirLife family of brands offers a product portfolio that spans the continuum of care from first responder to home care  with safety  patient comfort  and clinical performance in mind. JHNA is currently seeking a talented Senior Communications Network Systems engineer to support the Intelligent Teaming Branch of the Technology Development Directorate of Aviation and Missile Command at Ft Eustis  VA. Position: Systems Design Engineer - C/C++  Kernel development for AI/ML processor  performance modeling
Job_Description: We are looking for a dynamic  energetic Silicon Validation Lead to join our growing team in AI Group. In this role  the individual will be responsible for architecting and developing scalable silicon validation framework  defining kernel dataflow architecture  defining block level and system level tests for AI Engine (AIE) block for edge and cloud based platforms  ML model performance evaluation on AI Engine based silicon platforms  AIE instruction modeling  developing application specific kernels for AIE block  defining block and system level performance  developing performance tests  and test bring-up and debug on pre/post silicon platforms. This role expects the individual to drive the test plan  validation infrastructure  test bring-up and debug  driving automation framework and working with AIE architecture and design team to ensure functional and performance requirements are signed off. The team is dynamic and fast paced offering each of its members tremendous personal opportunity to grow their knowledge and skills in complex problem solving  product development and system engineering. As a Silicon Validation Lead  you will drive innovative  scalable  and automated silicon validation framework for AMD’s AI Engine block. In this position  your expertise on silicon validation of AI processors will be necessary towards product development  definition  and root cause resolution.

Job_Description: The Accessories Associate Designer will provide critical support to the Accessories Design Team throughout every aspect of the product creation process for The North Face technical and lifestyle gloves and headwear. You will be a crucial member of our team focused on creating innovative and technologically advanced products.    Join the North Face Family    The North Face was built on a love for the outdoors and the desire to enable all types of exploration  for all people  from their backyards to the Himalayas. Over the last 50 years we've lived by our “true north ” the belief that exploration has the power to change us  to challenge us and to help us see the world from new perspectives. To help ignite a global movement of outdoor exploration  love for the natural world and an unwavering commitment to protect it  we welcome and encourage new participants to the outdoors. We extend our reach through support of non-profit organizations  establishing programs that connect participants with close-to-home recreation opportunities  and creating a connection with young leaders  inspiring them to explore and conserve.    As we enter our sixth decade  we pledge to:    Accessories Associate Designer    Unless prohibited by applicable law  please note it is a condition of your employment to abide by Company policy  including VF's COVID-19 Vaccine Requirement Policy. In accordance with the policy  absent need for reasonable medical or religious accommodation or other exemption as allowed by state or local law  all eligible associates must present proof of being fully vaccinated for COVID-19 on the first day of employment. A copy of the policy and state specific addendum is attached for your reference.    How You Will Make a Difference       You will have the opportunity to support and grow alongside experienced creatives and gain valuable experience in all elements of the design process.       You will take notes at sample reviews  create and edit techpacks  color CADs  assist with file creation and organization  presentation preparation and market research. You will work cross functionally with the Graphics  Materials and Apparel teams.       You will be able to work independently to meet crucial deadlines and learn to anticipate the needs of our team throughout our calendar. You will wear many hats and the way in which you contribution to the team will evolve throughout the product creation process. You will stress the details  effectively communicate  be a team player and be committed to producing high quality work and always improving. You will grow in your roll and ultimately have the opportunity to work on your own designs.    Free to Be  Inclusion & Diversity    As a purpose-led  performance driven company  we strive to foster a culture of belonging based on respect  connection  openness  and authenticity. We are committed to building and maintaining a workplace that celebrates the diversity of our associates  allowing them to bring their authentic selves to work every day. Proficient in Adobe Illustrator and 2D product illustration. Familiarity in Photoshop  3D modeling a plus. Strong personal aesthetic and design principles Knowledge of outdoor industry trends Excellent time management and accountability Consistent attention to detail and shows initiative    Working knowledge and understanding of Accessories construction a plus Experience producing detailed techpacks a plus 3D modeling and Photoshop proficiency a plus Production and manufacturing knowledge a plus Understanding of outdoor sports (skiing  climbing  trail running  etc) a plus    What’s In It for You    We’re in the business of unleashing human potential  driven by the ideas  energy and commitment of our people. That’s why we offer comprehensive benefits that encourage mental  physical and financial well-being for all VF associates. When it comes to benefits  we’re the total package. Job_Description: Tired of designing the same old electrical panels job after job? Long for some eCAD variety? Looking for technically challenging projects  so you can learn something new  but still apply all that you know? DMC has a challenging opportunity for an electrical design professional who has a desire to advance and/or expand their technical skills  while providing top notch customer service. This is not your ordinary Electrical Designer/ eCAD position. This is an opportunity to collaborate with co-workers  customers  vendors  and partners - to put your problem-solving skills to work - and design cutting-edge Test and Measurement systems that delight our customers. You’ll become a key member of our team and encouraged to grow in your career. The Test and Measurement Electrical Designer will be responsible for working collaboratively with Test and Measurement Engineers to transform their project concept drawings into clear  concise  and standardized electrical drawings for manufacturing at the DMC fabrication Studio or using external build partners. Throughout the course of this work  they will communicate with both the engineering and fabrication teams to create ‘ready to build’ electrical-panel  rack sub-system  and full test equipment rack drawing packages. This work includes BOM finalization  rack and panel layouts  component rating/sizing  generating IO lists  and designing power distribution. After handoff of these materials for build  the Test and Measurement Electrical Designer will be a key reference and project resource for the assembly engineers and technicians. DMC’s Test and Measurement team works on a wide range of projects in a variety of industries from automotive to aero-space and defense  and everything in between. Our engineers and designers are constantly learning new technologies in order to continually provide cutting-edge solutions to our customers. At DMC  we maintain an active company culture  which includes weekly company-sponsored athletic  cultural  and social events. Full-time employees will enjoy a great benefits package including health  dental  and vision coverage as well as 401K matching  generous paid vacation time  and a well-stocked kitchen full of snacks. Additionally  we were recently named the #2 Best Mid-size Place to Work in Chicago by Crain’s!  Please note compensation is based on credentials and location: DMC typically evaluates compensation and grants raises on an annual basis (raise amounts are dependent on company and individual performance). DMC believes in rewarding employees for additional effort beyond what is expected. One of the ways we recognize employees is through Extra Effort bonuses  intended to reward employees for periods of working extremely long hours  working more than the occasional weekend  or other acts of extra effort. Additionally  DMC offers Site and Travel Compensation  which is intended to compensate employees for time spent working out of DMC's offices due to the travel requirements of the position. Perkins is more than a school; we are an international NGO dedicated to working in 100 countries for over 100 years to help children with multiple  complex disabilities and visual impairments and their families. We are unlocking opportunities and igniting change. At Perkins  we think courageously  we are collaborative and we take ownership. Join a community of growth! About Us: For over 30 years the Assistive Device Center has been designing and constructing individualized adaptive devices for children with multiple disabilities. The aim of the Assistive Device Center is to provide custom-made adaptive equipment and instructional materials to help support the educational and therapeutic goals of our students  allow them to better access their environment and to help them function to their highest capabilities. We provide materials to over 800 children across the state and produce over 1800 items a year. Summary The Assistive Device Center designer and fabricator/occupational therapist or physical therapist is involved in all aspects of production of custom-made equipment in the Assistive Device Center. This includes assessment of student needs  design of unique assistive devices  fabrication of equipment  supervision of volunteers  instruction for groups and individuals new to adaptive design  development of systems for tracking production  and information dissemination. Essential Duties  Responsibilities and Expectations include the following: Evaluate children in collaboration with teachers  therapists  other designers and/or family members to determine what custom-made adaptive equipment might best support the students’ educational objectives. This often takes the form of fitting children for modified seating and other positioning equipment. Design and construct unique solutions for unusual challenges for specific children to enable them to more fully access their environment and participate to their fullest extent in daily activities. Demonstrate competency in all aspects of production of custom-made assistive devices. Must have confidence in tool use and the ability to quickly learn skills in cardboard carpentry  woodworking  sewing  and plastics design. Maintain high standards to ensure that outgoing products are functional  safe  durable  and attractive. Establish and maintain a supportive community for the many volunteers who work in the Assistive Device Center. This will include setting up work activities to match the volunteers’ skills and interests and providing instruction for new individuals. Teach or co-teach classes in adaptive design. Introductory or hands-on instruction is offered in the Assistive Device Center at Perkins  at locations in other countries served by Perkins International  or in schools that have requested customized training. Provide individualized instruction for occupational therapy students in their Level II fieldwork placements  participants in the Perkins Educational Leadership Program  and others with a specialized interest in a customized internship. Participate in all routine aspects of production so as to ensure the continuous output of assistive devices that support the school Develop and maintain organizational systems to keep track of assistive device requests  streamline dissemination of plans to fabricators  and manage production data. Create illustrated directions for frequently made assistive devices. Update them as needed to make them as user-friendly as possible. Maintain the workshop space. This includes purchasing materials  maintaining tools  organizing supplies  and keeping the work areas clean. Share information about adaptive design. Update the Assistive Device Center presence on the Perkins website as needed. Maintain the “Lookbook” which describes the information needed from itinerant teachers when they request often-made projects. Maintain on-site photo galleries and displays. Develop online tutorials. Attend conferences  take courses  and/or visit other adaptive design programs to maintain certification and stay aware of current best practices. Assistive Device Designer and Fabricator Requirements Degree in chosen related service provider field. Current certifications and licenses as required by profession. Ability to carry 30 lbs and be able to stand for long periods of time. Excellent interpersonal communication skills. Ability to use tools safely and maintain a safe working environment. Ability to multitask and ensure the continuous flow of work. Good fine motor skills and attention to detail. Ability to retain large pieces of information and disseminate it to others. Preference given to: Occupational or Physical Therapist (Other related service providers  special educators or Assistive Technology Practitioners with experience in adaptive design considered. We have benefits that put you first  including an employer contributing retirement plan  tuition reimbursement from day one  professional development for our employees  personal days  paid time off and paid sick leave. Our campus is quaint  charming and historical  a perfect mix of legacy and modern buildings. It is located in the heart of Watertown  adjacent to the Charles River and a 5 minute drive from food & entertainment at Arsenal Yards. Posted: 7/24/2023

At MRM Global  we believe there is a better way to support customers with physical point of sale marketing. We believe that the future is on-demand ordering  localized content  and distributed production. Clients including as Bacardi  Diageo  Carlsberg  Pernod Ricard  and Molson Coors use our Brand Creator technology platform to create customized and brand compliant marketing materials that are produced on-demand through our cloud printing network. Although there will be future opportunities to work on a wider variety of design and content projects. Reporting to the VP of Operations USA  you will be required to work freely across a wide range of creative projects  both print and digital  delivering engaging and stand-out creative for our clients. As well as your salary: To deliver brilliant marketing to MRM’s global drinks suppliers and their customers we need to build a company that is reflective of their diversity. Job_Description: SUMMARY Performs layout and design  and assists with sales of wall panels and components while providing quality client service.  The pay range for this position is $72 000.00/yr - $98 400.00/yr depending on experience.  INTENT OF JOB DESCRIPTION AND MODIFICATION This job description describes the duties and responsibilities  qualification requirements  physical demands  work environment  etc. for this job. Duties may be combined with other jobs or duties from other jobs depending upon operational circumstances. Management reserves the right to add  modify or end any of the duties contained in the job description as business conditions warrant.  ESSENTIAL DUTIES AND RESPONSIBILITIES include the following. Other duties may be assigned.  1. Service current clients by responding to truss needs and concerns regarding truss quality. Visit clients work sites as needed to deliver bids  takeoffs  or to encourage further business dealings with the company. May also visit work sites to perform field measures or to ascertain construction or manufacturing defects.  2. Perform accurate and professional component designs using customer blueprints resulting in zero shrink. Review cutting lists  production reports and delivery schedules to ensure the quality of the final product and timely deliveries to customers.  3. Create accurate bids  and material and price lists for clients in a timely manner.  4. At the client’s request  provide engineered truss drawings to the client in a timely manner.  5. Provide technical knowledge and assistance to Layout Persons and Cutters in the designing of components and component layouts.  6. Provide technical support to internal and external clients including Foxworth-Galbraith sales associates  contractors and the general public.  7. Attend and participate in all Company sponsored training programs as required.  8. Perform any other duties  responsibilities or tasks as assigned.  SUPERVISORY RESPONSIBILITIES This job has no supervisory responsibilities.  QUALIFICATIONS To perform this job successfully  an individual must be able to perform each essential duty satisfactorily. The requirements listed below are representative of the knowledge  skill  and/or ability required. Reasonable accommodations may be made to enable individuals with disabilities to perform the essential functions.  EDUCATION and/or EXPERIENCE Bachelor's degree (B. A.) from four-year college or university; and four years related experience and/or training; or equivalent combination of education and experience.  LANGUAGE SKILLS Must have the ability to understand the English language in both the written and verbal form and to interpret documents such as safety rules  operating procedures  maintenance instructions  procedure manuals  work orders  takeoffs and engineered drawings. Ability to write routine reports and correspondence. Ability to speak effectively before groups of customers or associates of organization.  MATHEMATICAL SKILLS Ability to calculate figures and amounts such as discounts  interest  commissions  proportions  percentages  area  circumference  and volume. Ability to apply concepts of basic algebra and geometry.  REASONING ABILITY Ability to solve practical problems and deal with a variety of concrete variables in situations where only limited standardization exists. Ability to interpret a variety of instructions furnished in written  oral  diagram  or schedule form.  CERTIFICATES  LICENSES  REGISTRATIONS Driver’s License.  PHYSICAL DEMANDS The physical demands described here are representative of those that must be met by an associate to successfully perform the essential functions of this job. Reasonable accommodations may be made to enable individuals with disabilities to perform the essential functions.  While performing the duties of this job  the associate is regularly required to sit; use hands to finger  handle  or feel; reach with hands and arms; and talk or hear. The associate frequently is required to stand and walk. The associate must occasionally lift and/or move up to 50 pounds. Specific vision abilities required by this job include close vision  distance vision  color vision  peripheral vision  depth perception  and ability to adjust focus.  WORK ENVIRONMENT The work environment characteristics described here are representative of those an associate encounters while performing the essential functions of this job. Reasonable accommodations may be made to enable individuals with disabilities to perform the essential functions.  While performing the duties of this job  the associate is occasionally exposed to moving mechanical parts  fumes or airborne particles  risk of electrical shock and outside weather conditions. The noise level in the work environment is usually moderate.  OTHER SKILLS AND ABILITIES Professional level sales knowledge of building component design and manufacturing is required. The ability to use computers is required. Prior experience using truss planning software is required. A Technical Project Manager (TPM) leads complex IT  or engineering projects from initiation through implementation and deployment. Managing for highest-quality client experience and results by monitoring all project processes and operations for time and resource efficiencies  cost management  and process improvement opportunities. A TPM seldom participates directly in the activities that produce the end result  but rather stewards the progress  seamless collaboration and tasks of all stakeholders to maximize benefits and mitigate risks. The TPM is the conduit and connector of information  guiding a project to completion and providing support for project team members. TPMs coordinate across each level of the organization and across the integrated  cross-functional workflow. Objectively representing the time  resources  discipline  and risks associated with decision-making. The TPM acts as trusted advisor to functional leads  providing an objective view of total resources and capability to deliver on requirements. The includes risks to current project and potential ripple effects on other projects in process. Across the enterprise  TPMs collaborate with functional stakeholders in service of making more well-informed decisions and to properly advise clients on risks/rewards in real-time. With client intimacy at the forefront  TPMs are expected to exercise critical thinking to produce the highest levels of client satisfaction while balancing internal/external resources required to deliver best-in-class work. Success is demonstrated through the following: On time & within scope Resource management Enterprise project management tools Collaboration & engagement Feedback loop Communication Quality & Workflow Governance Resource & Risk Mitigation

Job_Description: The Project Manager is accountable for delivering procurement deliverables on assigned projects and agreed targets and goals to ensure product development milestones are achieved and material cost  delivery  and quality targets are realized while in compliance with relevant policies  standards  guidelines  and operating procedures. The role is responsible for ensuring the successful execution and completion of procurement deliverables on product development projects while leveraging category and supplier strategies to maximize value to the product portfolio. The Project Manager is responsible for selecting and developing suppliers in alignment with global category and supplier strategies in the pre-launch phase of product development. Azure Summit Technology is a mature  growing small business with locations in Melbourne  Florida  and Fairfax  Virginia. Azure develops and delivers high-performance RF hardware  firmware  and software products  and innovative  practical  multi-function RF systems solutions that address emerging missions of national importance for customers across the Department of Defense. We are a diverse team of highly qualified RF systems engineers and mission subject matter experts (SMEs) with backgrounds in electrical  mechanical  RF  hardware  software  firmware  and systems engineering  working together within a creative  innovative and highly collaborative culture  to deliver cutting edge solutions for our customers. To do this  we hire people with a passion to succeed. We look for problem solvers. People who have unique perspectives and diverse experience. Do you work well in a team environment and on your own as an individual contributor? Do you know how to set the bar high and achieve goals for yourself and bring others along with you? Do you work hard and play hard? Do you want to help the company succeed and build your skill set and further your career at the same time? Azure Summit Technology just might be the place for you. Azure Summit Technology provides a wide range of multi-channel  software-defined radio solutions for applications including surveillance  communications  radar  direction finding  emitter location  and interference cancellation. Systems can be tailored to meet a variety of requirements for bandwidth  dynamic range  number of channels  and computational resources. Supported platforms range from resource-constrained small UAVs and wearable devices to manned aircraft and submarines. Azure also offers innovative signal processing solutions to challenging problems in the realm of radio frequency spectrum awareness. Azure Summit Technology is currently seeking a Junior Java Software Engineer. The selected candidate will be part of a dynamic  growing  cross-functional  and geographically distributed team. This position is located on-site at our facility in Fairfax  Virginia  with occasional overnight travel to our office in Melbourne  Florida and/or other locations as needed to support customer activities. Your future team has worked together to produce the following job description: The selected candidate will design  develop  modify  integrate  and evaluate software for signals intelligence  radar  and communications systems. You will be instrumental in the software engineering of Java server applications using J2EE related technologies. Duties will include all aspects of software engineering  including requirements analysis and specification  software design  implementation and integration  testing  and installation. Astrobotic Technology  Inc. is a space robotics company that seeks to make space accessible to the world. The company’s suite of lunar landers delivers payloads to the Moon for companies  governments  universities  non-profits  and individuals. The company is also developing advanced space robotics capabilities such as terrain relative navigation  mobile robotics for lunar surface operations  and reliable computing systems for mission-critical applications. Originally spun out of Carnegie Mellon University in 2007  Astrobotic is pioneering affordable planetary access that promises to spark a new era of exploration  science  tourism  resource utilization  and mining. Astrobotic’s headquarters is in Pittsburgh  Pennsylvania  with a second location in Mojave  California. Astrobotic’s Lunar Surface Systems Department is seeking a software engineer to develop ground and flight software for our portfolio of cutting-edge solutions on the Lunar surface  particularly our Lunar rover and power product lines. With numerous flight opportunities  our surface assets will soon be flying to the Moon to demonstrate critical capabilities such as deploying Lunar power infrastructure  long-range communications  and autonomous surface operations. In this role  you will play a critical role in the development and maintenance of software systems that support ground-based operations and flight software for Lunar missions. You will be responsible for designing  implementing  and testing software solutions that enable efficient and reliable communication  data processing  and command execution between ground stations and spacecraft. Your expertise in programming languages  such as C++  Python  or Java  along with your knowledge of software engineering principles  will allow you to develop robust and scalable software architectures. Collaborating closely with cross-functional teams  including mission operations specialists and system engineers  you will contribute to the continuous improvement of ground software systems  ensuring their compatibility  efficiency  and adherence to industry standards. Your attention to detail  problem-solving skills  and ability to work in a fast-paced environment will be essential as you analyze requirements  debug issues  and optimize performance. The Lunar Surface Systems Department fosters a collaborative working environment with high degrees of freedom  responsibility  and expectations. We’re building novel solutions to challenging technical problems with the goal of making space more accessible to the world as a commercial platform. The company was recently selected by NASA as a premier organization to deliver American payloads to the Moon and leads the world in international payload sales. The company’s Peregrine lander will mark America’s return to Moon and is scheduled for launch in 2023. Note: This position may be filled at multiple levels  including Engineer II  Senior  Principal  etc. depending on the candidate’s experience. The Babyscripts Team is seeking a self-starting Mobile Software Engineer that will help continue to evolve our patient-facing mobile application’s functionality and architecture. The Software Engineer  Mobile  will be helping to improve maternal outcomes by putting the power of technology in the hands of moms-to-be. Babyscripts is a maternal digital health organization with the goal of Better Pregnancies for All. We provide a suite of products aimed at increasing access to care and improving outcomes. Our products aid in understanding and assessing risk early in the pregnancy to provide the patient and care team with the information that they need for the best care possible. The base of the Babyscripts solution is myJourney  a mobile app with thousands of pieces of clinically-validated content  delivered at the right time in the mom’s pregnancy journey. Built onto myJourney are modules tailored to a patient’s risk level to provide the best-fit support for that patient  while providing care providers with greater insight into the patient’s health and wellbeing. This is a full time salaried position offering competitive pay commensurate with experience.

Must have an overall business sense and understand how decisions impact business results.    Who We Hire?      Simply put  we hire everyone.
